EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 152300 UTC
INITIALLY A LARGE DEEP MULTI-CENTRED LOW PRESSURE WILL LIE MID-ATLANTIC
WITH A WEAK RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE ACROSS MUCH OF NITON. MONDAY THIS RIDGE
COLLAPSES AS A DEEP LOW CENTRE FM WITHIN THE PARENT LOW MOVS NE TOWARDS
ICELAND AND LOW PRESSURE INFLUENCE EXTENDS ACROSS NITON. WEDNESDAY THE MULTI-CENTRED
LOW MOVS CLOSER TO THE UK AND A SMALL AND POTENTIALLY DEEP LOW MAY DEVELOP
AND MOV ACROSS SHANNON AND THEN IRELAND. HOWEVER CONFIDENCE IS LOW REGARDING
THIS. STRG WINDS OR NEAR GALES DEVELOP ACROSS WERN AREAS ON SUNDAY NIGHT
AND PERSIST MONDAY MORNING. LATER MONDAY WINDS EASE A LITTLE LEAVING OCCASIONAL
STRG WINDS ACROSS ALL OF NITON. TUESDAY OCCASIONAL STRG WINDS OR NEAR GALES
ACROSS MUCH OF NITON. TUESDAY NIGHT NEAR GALES OR GALES ARE FCST TO SPREAD
